Dear John K. Johnstone,

Congratulations!  Your paper entitled "Rational control of orientation for
animation", co-authored with James P. Williams, has been accepted for
inclusion in the Graphics Interface'95 program.

In the following email message I am forwarding to you the referees'
comments.  Please give them serious consideration when preparing the final
version of your paper.

The author's kit will be sent to you next week by the proceedings editor,
Dr. Wayne Davis.  The kit contains complete information on the preparation
of your camera-ready manuscript.  An acknowledgment of receipt form will be
included in the kit.  If you have not received the kit by 15 February, 1995
please contact Dr. Davis at 604-494-9056 or by fax at 604-494-4033, or by
email at davis@cs.ualberta.ca.  The camera-ready manuscript is due March
25, 1995.

You will receive shortly a Preliminary Program indicating the date, time
and session in which your paper will be presented.  Closer to the time of
the conference you will be contacted regarding information as to which of
the authors (in the case of multiple authors) will be presenting and your
audio/visual requirements.

If your address has changed or if the kit should go to one of the other
authors, send a correction immediately to Dr. Davis.

I am looking forward to seeing you at the conference!

Yours sincerely,johnstone@cis.uab.edu
Dr. P. Prusinkiewicz
Program Chair, Graphics Interface'95



